  <title>Hello, writing</title>
  <link>https://derekwakefield.com/posts/2026-05-09-hello-writing.html</link>
  <description><![CDATA[ 





<p>This is the first post on the Writing page. If you can read it on the live site, the listing pipeline is working: a new <code>.qmd</code> file dropped into <code>posts/</code>, pushed, picked up by the Quarto build, and rendered on <code>/writing/</code> with title, date, and description.</p>
<section id="things-this-post-is-checking" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="things-this-post-is-checking">Things this post is checking</h2>
<p>A handful of formatting features get exercised below so we can see whether the theme renders them cleanly.</p>
<section id="inline-emphasis" class="level3">
<h3 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="inline-emphasis">Inline emphasis</h3>
<p>Italics with <em>single asterisks</em>. Bold with <strong>double asterisks</strong>. A link to <a href="https://quarto.org/docs/websites/website-listings.html">the Quarto docs</a> so we can see how external links style.</p>
</section>
<section id="a-callout" class="level3">
<h3 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="a-callout">A callout</h3>
<div class="callout callout-style-default callout-note callout-titled">
<div class="callout-header d-flex align-content-center">
<div class="callout-icon-container">
<i class="callout-icon"></i>
</div>
<div class="callout-title-container flex-fill">
Note
</div>
</div>
<div class="callout-body-container callout-body">
<p>This is a Quarto callout. If it shows up as a bordered box with a “Note” label, callouts work.</p>
</div>
</div>
</section>
